Package algorithms.shortestPaths

Class FloydWarshalAllPairs

java.lang.Object
algorithms.shortestPaths.FloydWarshalAllPairs
public class FloydWarshalAllPairs extends Object
from Cormen, Leiserson, Rivest, and Stein "Intro to Algorithms" finds shortest paths between all pairs of vertices in a directed graph with dynamic programming. The runtime complexity is O(|V|^3). Note: consider using DFS single source-all destination search on each vertex, making a worst case runtime complexity of O(|V|*(|V| + |E|)). W, D W is an nxn matrix of w[i][j] where each entry is the edge weight if any between i and j. has values 0 if i==j and inf where there is no connection. D is an nxn matrix of d[i][j] where each entry is the weight of the shortest path between i and j. d[i][j]_k = w[i][j] if k = 0 = min( d[i][k]_(k-1) + d[k][j]_(k-1) ) if k .geq. 1
